title: FedEx 's revenue 2009 to 2019
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Revenue in billion U.S. dollars, containing a total of 11 data points.
In general Revenue in billion U.S. dollars has rose over the Year.
Revenue in billion U.S. dollars is roughly constant from 2009 to 2010, slightly increasing from 2010 to 2011, roughly constant from 2011 to 2015, and finally gradually increasing from 2015 to 2019.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2016 and 2017.
The highest Revenue in billion U.S. dollars, of value 69.69 was reached at Year 2019
The lowest Revenue in billion U.S. dollars, of value 34.73 was reported at Year 2010
